{
  "text": "The doses of Epo were selected on the basis of the equivalent regimen used in humans with anaemia (the lower dose) and the higher dose group was one order of magnitude higher, assuming that conventional doses would be insufficient to negate the potent effect of Dox. Animals were maintained for 7 weeks after the last Dox injection, and during that period, death was recorded as well as body weight and general health assessment. At the end of the study, M-mode echocardiographic analysis of the heart was performed [CITATION_1] after which the animals were sacrificed. Upon sacrifice, blood was obtained for evaluation of haematological parameters, heart was divided into three sections for histological analysis, and spleen and bone marrow were obtained for the assessment of EPC number and function.",
